
// This Hyperlambda code sets the value of the [.content] node to the result of reading from a stream. The stream is obtained from the [file] node within the [.arguments] node, specifically from its [stream] child node. This operation effectively reads the content from the specified stream and assigns it to the [.content] node.
set-value:x:@.content
   io.stream.read:x:@.arguments/*/file/*/stream
